comment:
* A few Calendar globals are needed in the CalendarProvider for expanding
     * the Instances table and these are all stored in the first (and only) row
     * of the CalendarMetaData table.
     *
     * @hide

variables.name: LOCAL_TIMEZONE
variables.comment:
* The local timezone that was used for precomputing the fields
         * in the Instances table.

variables.name: MIN_INSTANCE
variables.comment:
* The minimum time used in expanding the Instances table, * in UTC milliseconds. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: MAX_INSTANCE
variables.comment:
* The maximum time used in expanding the Instances table, * in UTC milliseconds. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: MIN_EVENTDAYS
variables.comment:
* The minimum Julian day in the EventDays table. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: MAX_EVENTDAYS
variables.comment:
* The maximum Julian day in the EventDays table. *

Type: INTEGER
